nl.fw.yapool

Class PoolUsageLogger

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.fw.yapool.PoolUsageLogger
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable

    public class PoolUsageLogger
extends Object
implements Runnable
    Logs a pruned pool's performance at regular intervals using all readily available counters and sizes (there is no performance impact on the pool itself). E.g. a log-statement could look like:
    PoolName size: 10, leased: 6, idle: 4, created: 1, EXPIRED: 1
    If values do not change or are of no interest (zero), nothing is logged. If nothing happens with the pool, no log statement will appear.
    Author:
    FWiers
